    353          /*********************************************************************
    354          *
    355          *       _WriteBlocking()
    356          *
    357          *  Function description
    358          *    Stores a specified number of characters in SEGGER RTT ring buffer
    359          *    and updates the associated write pointer which is periodically
    360          *    read by the host.
    361          *    The caller is responsible for managing the write chunk sizes as
    362          *    _WriteBlocking() will block until all data has been posted successfully.
    363          *
    364          *  Parameters
    365          *    pRing        Ring buffer to post to.
    366          *    pBuffer      Pointer to character array. Does not need to point to a \0 terminated string.
    367          *    NumBytes     Number of bytes to be stored in the SEGGER RTT control block.
    368          *
    369          *  Return value
    370          *    >= 0 - Number of bytes written into buffer.
    371          */

